docs.abstract: As the maker of ChatGPT battles Google and Meta for A.I. supremacy, it’s also fighting to end control by a nonprofit board.
docs.snippet: As the maker of ChatGPT battles Google and Meta for A.I. supremacy, it’s also fighting to end control by a nonprofit board.
docs.lead_paragraph: Last fall, the nonprofit that controls OpenAI tried to fire the company’s high-profile leader, Sam Altman. It failed.

headline.main: How OpenAI Hopes to Sever Its Nonprofit Roots
headline.print_headline: OpenAI Is Trying To Redefine Its Identity

byline.original: By David A. Fahrenthold, Cade Metz and Mike Isaac

docs.abstract: The OpenAI C.E.O. spoke with Andrew Ross Sorkin at the DealBook Summit.
docs.snippet: The OpenAI C.E.O. spoke with Andrew Ross Sorkin at the DealBook Summit.
docs.lead_paragraph: Since kicking off the artificial intelligence boom with the launch of ChatGPT in 2022, OpenAI has amassed more than 300 million weekly users and a $157 billion valuation. Its C.E.O., Sam Altman, addressed whether that staggering pace of growth can continue at the DealBook Summit last week.

headline.main: Sam Altman on Microsoft, Trump and Musk

byline.original: By Andrew Ross Sorkin and Sarah Kessler

docs.lead_paragraph: One way to understand the video game industry’s current crisis is by looking closely at Spider-Man’s spandex.

headline.print_headline: Video Games Can’t Afford to Look So Good

docs.abstract: The rural region is changing fast as electricians from around the country plug the tech industry’s new, giant data centers into its ample power supply.
docs.snippet: The rural region is changing fast as electricians from around the country plug the tech industry’s new, giant data centers into its ample power supply.
docs.lead_paragraph: The tangy smell of Buffalo wings filled Side Chicks Sport Bar, as a dozen electricians crammed their big frames into booths. It was Tuesday night in East Wenatchee, Wash., and “brotherhood night” for the electrical union. Out-of-towners and locals swapped notes on who was coming and going, when new jobs were starting and what drama had gone down with a foreman.

headline.main: A.I., the Electricians and the Boom Towns of Central Washington
headline.print_headline: Data Centers Are Fueling a New Gold Rush

byline.original: By Karen Weise and Jovelle Tamayo
